{{Orphan|date=May 2016}}
In [[systems engineering]], the '''tricotyledon theory of system design (T3SD)''' is a [[mathematics|mathematical]] theory of system design developed by [[A. Wayne Wymore]].<ref name="wymore">{{cite book|last=Wymore|first=A. Wayne|authorlink=A. Wayne Wymore|title=Model-Based Systems Engineering|publisher=CRC Press, Inc.|year=1993|isbn = 084938012X}}</ref> T3SD consists of a language for describing [[system]]s and [[requirement]]s, which is based on [[set theory]], a mathematical systems model based on port automata, and a precise definition of the different types of system requirements and relationships between requirements.
== System requirements model == * I/O requirement * Performance requirement * System test requirement * Cost requirement * Tradeoff requirement
== System design == * Based on set theory * Transition systems * Functional system design * Buildable system design
